Application Framework: Django (DRF)/FastAPI
Cashing System: Redis
DBMS: PostgreSQL
Monitoring System: Grafana/Prometheus

div.div:
For web server we have several options but most famous technologies are Nginx and Apache. Cause we are using Docker and Docker itself is Linux base, i choose Nginx that more compatible with Linux than Apache.
For application framework selection i personally use FastAPI for this kind of projects. Better Asynchronous Programming Process, Dependency injection , Auto Documentation and Response/Request Schemas are the pros of using this framework.
But base on task document, i should do it with Django (DRF) so i choose this framework.
For Caching System i know two Caching System Technologies, Redis and Infinispan.
Base on my (and also other developers in community) knowledge in these technologies, I select Redis for having optimal expense (Technical) to use these type of technologies.
For DB the first question that i have to answer is SQL or NoSQL?
This is an interview tasks with lightweight tasks and endpoints. Also we need to select Consistency rather than Availability (CAP Theorem)
I do not have a perfect vision for Read/Write tasks amount in this project to select between Read friendly or Write friendly DBs.
So i selected SQL for making sure that data are consistent in DB (Using Transactions).
In SQL DBMSs i selected PostgreSQL to have better compatibility with Django.
For monitoring systems dashboard i choose Grafana and for collecting data from other parts like application and db i use Prometheus
